The paper is about music genre classification, which falls under the umbrella of music information retrieval (MIR). The paper discusses various techniques and datasets used for music genre classification, as well as new trends in machine learning applied to the music annotation problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
